# jfc runtime state (caches, task store, pending learning, skills usage,
# audit ledgers, change-sets, …) is all per-run noise — ignore the whole
# .jfc/ tree by default, then re-include only the deliberately-tracked
# project config dirs (agents, memory, workflows, plans). This catches new
# runtime subdirs (e.g. .jfc/skills/) automatically without growing the list.
.jfc/*
!.jfc/agents/
!.jfc/memory/
!.jfc/workflows/
!.jfc/plans/
# Per-crate runtime state dirs created when running jfc from a subdir.
crates/**/.jfc/

# Agent runtime state (exec-call captures)
.code/
